ith an ageing population and increasing awareness of adult abuse and neglect, the importance of effective safeguarding practices cannot be overstated. In this blog, Rose Mabiza explores the significance of safeguarding adults, relevant legislation, best practice guidelines, and practical recommendations for professionals in social care settings.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-3385_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-3380_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-3372_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-3464_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-3384_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Navigating_Legislation_ComplyPlus_for_Children_s_Home_Regulations_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1710431109" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Navigating_Legislation_ComplyPlus_for_Children_s_Home_Regulations_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1710431109 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Navigating_Legislation_ComplyPlus_for_Children_s_Home_Regulations_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1500x.jpg?v=1710431109 1280w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Navigating_Legislation_ComplyPlus_for_Children_s_Home_Regulations_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.jpg?v=1710431109 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Navigating_Legislation_ComplyPlus_for_Children_s_Home_Regulations_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1710431109 320w" width="1612" height="1228" alt="Mastering Safeguarding Adults (Social Care): Essential Training and Certification - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Mastering Safeguarding Adults (Social Care): Essential Training and Certification - ComplyPlus LMS™ - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-jQrDum jseZXh pf-3381_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-eLwHnm fPjVqe pf-3383_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by  Rawpixel via Envato Elements</p></div></div></div><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eGPXGI hfOvrX pf-3379_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-3374_ pf-text-1">According to the Office for National Statistics, there were an estimated 58,810 adults at risk of abuse in England in 2020-2021.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-3376_ pf-text-1">The National Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Adults (NSPCA) reports that around 1 in 6 adults over the age of 60 experience some form of abuse.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-hAcGzb caRPsV pf-3378_ pf-text-1">Research by Action on Elder Abuse suggests that only a fraction of abuse cases are reported, highlighting the need for improved safeguarding measures.</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-3398_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-3397_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-hmjpVf IvCUC pf-3391_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions</h3><div class="sc-jrQzAO jIEVBe pf-3465_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gIDmLj bESFPC pf-3389_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Protecting_Vulnerable_Adults_Social_Care_Safeguarding_Strategies_and_Best_Practices_-_ComplyPlus_LMS_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=17133626